@*
    Help.cshtml - Help documentation view for PcApprovalAction component
*@
<div class="help-content">
    <h4>Approval Action Component</h4>
    
    <p>
        This component renders approve, reject, and delegate buttons for processing approval requests.
        Each button opens a modal dialog for entering comments before submitting the action.
    </p>
    
    <h5>Actions</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Approve</strong>: Advances the request to the next approval step, or marks the request as 
            fully approved if this is the final step in the workflow.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Reject</strong>: Marks the request as rejected. A reason for rejection is required.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Delegate</strong>: Allows reassigning the approval request to another user who will then 
            be responsible for taking action.
        </li>
    </ul>
    
    <h5>Configuration Options</h5>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>Request ID</strong>: Data source binding for the approval request ID. Use a data source 
            expression like <code>{{"{{Record.id}}"}}</code> to bind to a record property.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Show Approve Button</strong>: Toggle visibility of the approve button.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Show Reject Button</strong>: Toggle visibility of the reject button.
        </li>
        <li>
            <strong>Show Delegate Button</strong>: Toggle visibility of the delegate button.
        </li>
    </ul>
    
    <h5>Behavior</h5>
    <p>
        Action buttons are only enabled when:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>The request status is "pending"</li>
        <li>The current user is an authorized approver for the current workflow step</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        When the request is in any other status (approved, rejected, escalated, expired), 
        an informative message is displayed instead of the action buttons.
    </p>
</div>

